It's late.

59
00:03:42.255 --> 00:03:43.558
Yeah. my computer
crashed at home.

60
00:03:43.691 --> 00:03:45.593
I've got some schematics
that I need to finish.

61
00:03:47.260 --> 00:03:49.229
Check in at the front desk.

62
00:03:51.532 --> 00:03:54.836
-[guard 2] ID. handprint.
-Yeah. [sighs softly]

63
00:03:56.904 --> 00:03:59.306
-[beeping and whirring]
-[guard 2] Where you headed?

64
00:03:59.907 --> 00:04:01.209
Lower 15th. R&D.

65
00:04:01.809 --> 00:04:03.276
[guard 2]
It's a classified wing.

66
00:04:03.745 --> 00:04:05.513
-Yeah. I'm cleared.
-[radio buzzes]

67
00:04:05.646 --> 00:04:08.616
B-Team. Have a Ross Vilmore
headed your way.

68
00:04:09.784 --> 00:04:11.418
-Yeah. I know.
-[radio buzzes]

69
00:04:12.319 --> 00:04:13.320
What's the. uh...

70
00:04:13.453 --> 00:04:15.156
Section 34.

71
00:04:15.288 --> 00:04:16.824
Thirty-four. Standby.

72
00:04:16.958 --> 00:04:18.526
just double-checking
your clearance.

73
00:04:18.960 --> 00:04:21.294
Do you mind if I snag
some of that coffee?

74
00:04:21.896 --> 00:04:22.697
Sure.

75
00:04:22.830 --> 00:04:24.866
[music continues]

76
00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:28.569
[beeping]

77
00:04:28.936 --> 00:04:32.272
Uh. you got any creamer?

78
00:04:34.075 --> 00:04:35.109
Do I look like a barista?

79
00:04:35.243 --> 00:04:37.178
[rain spattering]

80
00:04:37.310 --> 00:04:38.445
[keyboard clacking]

81
00:04:38.579 --> 00:04:41.348
[beeping and whirring]

82
00:04:42.517 --> 00:04:44.852
I know that. uh.
Bob. he keeps some

83
00:04:44.986 --> 00:04:46.754
in his special drawer
in the bottom.

84
00:04:52.459 --> 00:04:54.729
Okay. ICE is in. We're ghosted.

85
00:04:54.862 --> 00:04:57.231
Visual. sensor. thermal. sound.

86
00:04:57.364 --> 00:04:58.331
Good.

87
00:04:58.900 --> 00:05:01.803
[Ross]
Hero! There we go.

88
00:05:07.608 --> 00:05:09.342
-[radio buzzes]
-[guard 2] Copy that.

89
00:05:10.211 --> 00:05:12.345
Okay. you're cleared. Lift four.

90
00:05:12.479 --> 00:05:14.916
Yes. Thank you for the coffee.

91
00:05:16.918 --> 00:05:20.353
-[engine whirring]
-[clacks]

92
00:05:20.988 --> 00:05:23.257
[doors rattling]

93
00:05:23.390 --> 00:05:25.793
[music continues]

94
00:05:32.166 --> 00:05:35.102
-[static crackling]
-[whirring and beeping]

95
00:05:43.376 --> 00:05:44.512
[guard 3]
Clear.

96
00:05:54.354 --> 00:05:56.757
[fan rumbling slowly]

97
00:06:03.164 --> 00:06:04.265
[zipper opens]

98
00:06:04.397 --> 00:06:05.733
We're in the outer passageway.

99
00:06:05.867 --> 00:06:06.767
Copy.

100
00:06:07.668 --> 00:06:08.769
[soft beep]

101
00:06:09.337 --> 00:06:12.006
Three levels down. South side.

102
00:06:14.542 --> 00:06:15.643
[zipper closes]

103
00:06:21.515 --> 00:06:23.818
[high-pitched whirring]

104
00:06:23.951 --> 00:06:25.987
[music increases]

105
00:06:28.322 --> 00:06:30.558
[soft beeping]

106
00:06:34.394 --> 00:06:36.631
[beeping increases]

107
00:06:37.832 --> 00:06:40.400
Triad 35B
by BT Security Concepts.

108
00:06:40.534 --> 00:06:42.136
It is pricey.

109
00:06:42.270 --> 00:06:44.305
-[loud beep]
-C4?

110
00:06:44.437 --> 00:06:46.073
Mm-mm. Knockout gas.

111
00:06:46.207 --> 00:06:49.476
-[beep]
-[grunts] Probably more
on each floor.

112
00:06:51.946 --> 00:06:53.080
Finders keepers.

113
00:06:58.052 --> 00:07:00.453
-[beeps]
-[automated voice]
<i>Access granted.</i>

114
00:07:05.259 --> 00:07:06.661
-[beeps]
-[door opens]

115
00:07:10.932 --> 00:07:13.167
-[whirrs]
-[keyboard clacking]

116
00:07:14.502 --> 00:07:17.738
[beeping and whirring]

117
00:07:19.307 --> 00:07:21.242
[keyboard clacking]

118
00:07:21.375 --> 00:07:23.611
[music continues]

119
00:07:26.113 --> 00:07:27.048
[beeps]

120
00:07:27.615 --> 00:07:30.017
-[whirring]
-[door opens]

121
00:07:45.498 --> 00:07:47.368
-Okay. we're clear. ETA?
-[crackling]

122
00:07:47.501 --> 00:07:50.237
Three minutes.
about to head into the vents
above your sector.

123
00:07:52.807 --> 00:07:54.408
-[thud]
-Sweet cut.

124
00:07:54.542 --> 00:07:55.743
[sighs softly]

125
00:08:03.684 --> 00:08:05.920
[beeping and whirring]

126
00:08:07.021 --> 00:08:08.356
[guard]
Hey! [grunts]

127
00:08:08.923 --> 00:08:11.158
-[grunting and groaning]
-[thudding]

128
00:08:14.428 --> 00:08:16.063
-[electricity crackling]
-[shouts]

129
00:08:17.698 --> 00:08:20.801
[breathes loudly]

130
00:08:22.403 --> 00:08:25.973
-Amateur. huh?
-The most important thing is...

131
00:08:26.374 --> 00:08:27.274
He's alive.

132
00:08:27.408 --> 00:08:28.242
You got it.

133
00:08:28.376 --> 00:08:30.611
[light tense music]

134
00:08:34.515 --> 00:08:36.183
[Ross]
I'm at the target. ETA?

135
00:08:36.317 --> 00:08:38.185
[Crilenger]
<i>Copy that. ETA. one minute.</i>

136
00:08:39.220 --> 00:08:40.955
[creaking]

137
00:08:50.998 --> 00:08:52.400
[footsteps approaching]

138
00:08:52.533 --> 00:08:54.035
Handprint and access card.

139
00:08:56.404 --> 00:08:57.538
[Ross]
Mm-hmm.

140
00:08:58.372 --> 00:09:00.941
[beeping and whirring]

141
00:09:02.176 --> 00:09:03.077
Your turn.

142
00:09:07.516 --> 00:09:08.549
How'd you get that?

143
00:09:09.283 --> 00:09:11.819
-[beeping and whirring]
-These scanners
are easy to hack.

144
00:09:13.320 --> 00:09:15.256
Mm-hmm. Did you make it?

145
00:09:16.390 --> 00:09:17.558
Shut up.

146
00:09:17.691 --> 00:09:19.060
-[zipper closes]
-Key card. Z.

147
00:09:22.997 --> 00:09:25.199
-[beeping and whirring]
-[door opens]

148
00:09:26.834 --> 00:09:29.303
[whooshing]

149
00:09:29.437 --> 00:09:31.839
[music increases]

150
00:09:38.846 --> 00:09:40.714
Oh. you didn't say anything
about two.

151
00:09:41.449 --> 00:09:44.452
Well. one's a display model.
Needed to delete all the files.

152
00:09:44.618 --> 00:09:47.588
then upload a virus
and steal everything.
That was the deal.

153
00:09:48.756 --> 00:09:50.157
That was not our deal.

154
00:09:50.891 --> 00:09:53.127
Look. like I said.
steal everything.

155
00:09:53.928 --> 00:09:55.596
And who cares?
We got the sphere.

156
00:09:56.931 --> 00:09:58.365
Right? Come on!

157
00:10:02.103 --> 00:10:03.270
Did you wipe
the security cameras.

158
00:10:03.404 --> 00:10:05.239
the card swipes.
and the security logs?

159
00:10:05.372 --> 00:10:08.809
Yeah. but we only
have five minutes
before the system reboots.

160
00:10:10.144 --> 00:10:11.312
Oh. fuck!

161
00:10:11.445 --> 00:10:12.646
What?

162
00:10:12.780 --> 00:10:14.148
I left the flash drive
in the office.

163
00:10:14.281 --> 00:10:16.417
Well. go fucking get it. then.
Let's go. Fast!

164
00:10:16.851 --> 00:10:17.985
[Ross softly]
Dang it.

165
00:10:21.222 --> 00:10:22.156
[door locks]

166
00:10:26.528 --> 00:10:28.462
-[siren blaring]
-[beeping]

167
00:10:28.597 --> 00:10:30.164
[whirring]

168
00:10:30.297 --> 00:10:31.566
[door closes]

169
00:10:31.699 --> 00:10:33.535
[automated voice]
<i>Intruder alert.</i>

170
00:10:33.667 --> 00:10:35.169
<i>Lockdown in progress.</i>

171
00:10:35.302 --> 00:10:36.804
That fucking Judas!

172
00:10:36.937 --> 00:10:38.540
-[whirring]
<i>-...authorized.</i>

173
00:10:38.906 --> 00:10:40.741
-Z. cover!
-[blaring continues]

174
00:10:40.875 --> 00:10:43.110
[gunshots]

175
00:10:44.678 --> 00:10:46.413
[glass shattering]

176
00:10:59.026 --> 00:11:01.328
[whirring and creaking]

177
00:11:01.462 --> 00:11:03.697
[ominous music]

178
00:11:04.365 --> 00:11:06.267
[doors rattling]

179
00:11:11.972 --> 00:11:14.208
[breathing heavily]

180
00:11:22.617 --> 00:11:23.417
-[beeps]
-[thud]

181
00:11:23.552 --> 00:11:25.654
[hissing]

182
00:11:25.819 --> 00:11:26.987
[guard shouts]
Ambush!

183
00:11:27.121 --> 00:11:29.356
-[beeping and whirring]
-[thudding]

184
00:11:29.490 --> 00:11:30.424
[Z exhales]

185
00:11:30.958 --> 00:11:32.760
-[gunshots]
-[crackling]

186
00:11:32.893 --> 00:11:35.129
[music increases]

187
00:11:42.036 --> 00:11:44.673
-[rain spattering]
-[automated voice on PA]
<i>Economic disparity</i>

188
00:11:44.805 --> 00:11:46.941
<i>has led a surge in violent crime</i>

189
00:11:47.074 --> 00:11:48.976
<i>-and property theft.</i>
-[siren blaring in the distance]

190
00:11:49.109 --> 00:11:50.744
<i>Aurora LTD...</i>
[continues indistinctly]

191
00:11:50.878 --> 00:11:53.147
-[clanking]
-[Ross grunts]

192
00:12:04.758 --> 00:12:05.660
Fuck.

193
00:12:06.927 --> 00:12:10.632
-[indistinct shouting on TV]
-[cell phone buzzing
and ringing]

194
00:12:10.764 --> 00:12:12.199
-[beep]
-[gunshots on video game]

195
00:12:12.333 --> 00:12:13.867
[Malik]
Good news only.

196
00:12:14.201 --> 00:12:16.070
-[rain spattering]
-Yeah. I did what you said.

197
00:12:16.203 --> 00:12:18.640
-So you have it?
<i>-Yeah. I got the chip.</i>

198
00:12:19.006 --> 00:12:21.976
<i>What about the mercs?</i>
<i>Crilenger and Z.</i>

199
00:12:22.109 --> 00:12:23.578
Well. they're trapped inside.

200
00:12:23.712 --> 00:12:25.647
So you didn't fuck it up.

201
00:12:26.213 --> 00:12:28.916
-What about the money?
<i>-Good things come</i>

202
00:12:29.049 --> 00:12:32.052
to he who does not piss me off.

203
00:12:32.453 --> 00:12:33.320
[beeps]

204
00:12:33.787 --> 00:12:36.056
Are you fucking serious.
you asshole?

205
00:12:36.658 --> 00:12:38.325
[thunder rumbling
in the distance]

206
00:12:38.459 --> 00:12:41.061
[automated voice on PA
speaks indistinctly]

207
00:12:42.496 --> 00:12:44.298
[reporter]
<i>A major break-in</i>
<i>at Peredor Corporation's</i>

208
00:12:44.431 --> 00:12:46.267
<i>research and development</i>
<i>facility last night</i>

209
00:12:46.400 --> 00:12:48.603
<i>has led to a frenzy</i>
<i>in the trade lines.</i>

210
00:12:48.737 --> 00:12:51.005
<i>Stockbrokers desperately</i>
<i>sell off Peredor's shares</i>

211
00:12:51.138 --> 00:12:54.375
<i>-based on rumors</i>
<i>of stolen trade secrets.</i>
-[indistinct chatter]

212
00:12:54.509 --> 00:12:57.044
<i>Many had purchased futures</i>
<i>on a promising new breakthrough</i>

213
00:12:57.177 --> 00:12:58.613
<i>Peredor hoped to deliver</i>
<i>to the market</i>

214
00:12:58.747 --> 00:13:00.781
<i>by the fourth quarter</i>
<i>of next year.</i>

215
00:13:00.914 --> 00:13:04.151
<i>Police authorities on the scene</i>
<i>were denied access</i>
<i>to the building.</i>

216
00:13:04.285 --> 00:13:06.387
<i>and Peredor has yet</i>
<i>to press any charges.</i>

217
00:13:06.521 --> 00:13:09.156
<i>According to their</i>
<i>public relations bureau.</i>

218
00:13:09.290 --> 00:13:11.892
<i>the investigation</i>
<i>is being conducted in-house</i>

219
00:13:12.026 --> 00:13:13.827
<i>by a private security team.</i>

220
00:13:14.228 --> 00:13:15.829
You know how much money
I'm about to lose?

221
00:13:15.963 --> 00:13:18.399
[Megan] It's a good time
to buy right now.
It is going cheap.

222
00:13:18.533 --> 00:13:21.802
You're right. I mean.
I bought a ton of Peredor
before this dog shit.

223
00:13:21.935 --> 00:13:23.571
Okay. do you want a Xanax?

224
00:13:24.138 --> 00:13:25.607
I already had two this morning.

225
00:13:26.273 --> 00:13:27.676
[Megan]
Crunching numbers. Ethan?

226
00:13:27.808 --> 00:13:29.778
[indistinct chatter continues]

227
00:13:29.910 --> 00:13:31.513
Earth to Ethan.

228
00:13:33.180 --> 00:13:34.481
Barrington Tran
Security Concepts

229
00:13:34.616 --> 00:13:36.551
made quite a lot of money
off of that contract

230
00:13:36.685 --> 00:13:38.185
for those new AI drones.

231
00:13:38.319 --> 00:13:40.287
-I mean. I bought a ton of that.
didn't you?
-Yep.

232
00:13:40.755 --> 00:13:42.657
Sad how many kids
have to be killed
by those things. though. huh?

233
00:13:42.791 --> 00:13:45.292
[clicks tongue]
Trade 'em as you see 'em. pal.

234
00:13:47.261 --> 00:13:49.196
-What is this?
-[paper rustling]

235
00:13:49.330 --> 00:13:51.398
That is confidential. good sir.

236
00:13:52.199 --> 00:13:53.802
Christ. Seriously?

237
00:13:53.934 --> 00:13:55.402
-[Harrison] Yo--
-Market didn't close.

238
00:13:55.537 --> 00:13:56.870
-[Harrison] Just about--
-Get back on the floor and make

239
00:13:57.004 --> 00:13:57.905
-some fucking money!
-Right away.

240
00:13:58.038 --> 00:13:58.939
[Harrison]
Got it.

241
00:13:59.073 --> 00:14:00.207
[Megan softly]
Go.

242
00:14:02.376 --> 00:14:03.844
[Kerry]
You get all P&L reports

243
00:14:03.977 --> 00:14:05.279
for every portfolio
up to quarter four?

244
00:14:05.412 --> 00:14:07.081
[clicks tongue] Yes. I did.

245
00:14:08.082 --> 00:14:11.485
-Good shit.
-Kerry. I am surprised.

246
00:14:11.619 --> 00:14:12.853
Is that a compliment?

247
00:14:12.986 --> 00:14:14.221
Fuck no.

248
00:14:15.456 --> 00:14:18.025
FYI. board meeting. High noon.

249
00:14:18.158 --> 00:14:20.294
Oh. and Wellman wants
to see you after.

250
00:14:20.427 --> 00:14:22.029
[phone ringing in the distance]

251
00:14:23.364 --> 00:14:24.965
It's always nice
to see you. Kerry.

252
00:14:25.099 --> 00:14:27.167
[Kerry]
Nice drawing. asshole.

253
00:14:29.804 --> 00:14:31.038
I think he likes me.

254
00:14:31.573 --> 00:14:34.942
Aside from all the boo-hooing
about the situation on Peredor.

255
00:14:35.075 --> 00:14:36.910
they run a tight ship.
They'll bounce back.

256
00:14:37.044 --> 00:14:39.046
Put that fucking phone down!

257
00:14:41.549 --> 00:14:43.752
We have healthy projections
in many sectors.

258
00:14:43.884 --> 00:14:45.452
But let's make this very clear.

259
00:14:45.587 --> 00:14:47.522
This is where we place our focus
over the next quarter.

260
00:14:47.655 --> 00:14:49.524
[clears throat]
This is from Wellman.

261
00:14:49.657 --> 00:14:52.926
Yeah. Harrison.
Straight from God Himself.
Can I finish now?

262
00:14:53.561 --> 00:14:54.562
Sorry.

263
00:14:54.696 --> 00:14:56.196
Anyway. Peredor Corporation.

264
00:14:56.330 --> 00:14:58.999
Sakura Biotech.
and Tranceworld Media.

265
00:14:59.366 --> 00:15:02.269
Don't trade against them.
And do not. I repeat.

266
00:15:02.403 --> 00:15:04.639
<i>do not</i> short their shit. Okay?

267
00:15:04.773 --> 00:15:07.274
No credit default swaps.
no naked shorts. nothing.

268
00:15:07.408 --> 00:15:09.744
But what if we get some huge...
[chuckles] buyer?

269
00:15:09.878 --> 00:15:11.579
Straight from fucking God!

270
00:15:12.814 --> 00:15:14.114
What about C & Earth?

271
00:15:14.549 --> 00:15:15.449
Fuck 'em.

272
00:15:15.817 --> 00:15:18.051
[suspenseful music]

273
00:15:21.021 --> 00:15:24.626
It's kinda strange
Kerry's asking us
to compartmentalize investments.

274
00:15:25.159 --> 00:15:26.493
It's strategic.

275
00:15:27.127 --> 00:15:30.330
-Yeah. [softly] Strategic.
-[phone ringing]

276
00:15:32.032 --> 00:15:33.467
Well. I'll see you
around. Megan.

277
00:15:34.636 --> 00:15:35.537
All right.

278
00:15:41.375 --> 00:15:45.647
Welcome. Ethan.
Would you like my assistant
to get you an espresso.

279
00:15:45.780 --> 00:15:47.549
bottled water. cream soda?

280
00:15:47.981 --> 00:15:48.883
[Ethan]
No. thank you.

281
00:15:49.551 --> 00:15:52.787
We read your reports.
Did you find any irregularities?

282
00:15:53.220 --> 00:15:54.689
Not that I know of.

283
00:15:55.857 --> 00:15:57.491
Do you like working here. Ethan?

284
00:15:58.893 --> 00:16:01.094
There's a lot of people
in the world
who don't have jobs.

285
00:16:01.796 --> 00:16:04.231
Guess I'm not
in a position to complain.

286
00:16:04.364 --> 00:16:05.733
Is there something
wrong with my work?

287
00:16:06.200 --> 00:16:10.237
No! On the contrary.
you're great at dissecting
the numbers.

288
00:16:10.872 --> 00:16:14.876
But... we've been running
the show here for a long time.

289
00:16:15.008 --> 00:16:17.211
and it's more than just numbers.

290
00:16:17.679 --> 00:16:19.714
Uh. we set the stage

291
00:16:19.848 --> 00:16:22.584
for how value
is perceived in the world.

292
00:16:22.717 --> 00:16:24.117
You could say that the...

293
00:16:24.251 --> 00:16:25.419
[chuckles softly]

294
00:16:25.553 --> 00:16:27.120
...the economy
is a marionette doll

295
00:16:27.254 --> 00:16:29.056
and we own the strings.

296
00:16:29.189 --> 00:16:30.457
Of course.

297
00:16:31.291 --> 00:16:35.028
-What do you want from me?
-Well. we're a little concerned
about exposure.

298
00:16:37.097 --> 00:16:37.932
Like?

299
00:16:38.065 --> 00:16:39.534
Market manipulation.

300
00:16:39.667 --> 00:16:42.202
Right. As a matter of fact.
if anything like that

301
00:16:42.336 --> 00:16:45.138
were going on here
at Mutual One and word got out.

302
00:16:45.573 --> 00:16:47.642
that would be a serious problem.

303
00:16:47.775 --> 00:16:49.409
Oh. yes. Of course.

304
00:16:52.179 --> 00:16:54.047
These are the new figures
for next quarter.

305
00:16:54.414 --> 00:16:56.350
Read them over.
Highlight anything unusual.

306
00:16:56.718 --> 00:16:58.520
Make sure
the projections add up.

307
00:16:59.219 --> 00:17:00.287
I can do that.

308
00:17:00.420 --> 00:17:02.256
-When do you need them by?
-Friday.

309
00:17:03.558 --> 00:17:05.927
We'd also like to keep
this matter private.

310
00:17:06.059 --> 00:17:07.562
Just between us. okay?

311
00:17:08.495 --> 00:17:11.231
-Yes. sir.
-Good. If you have
any questions.

312
00:17:11.365 --> 00:17:13.033
Kerry will address them for you.

313
00:17:13.166 --> 00:17:16.103
I will ask Kerry
all of my questions.

314
00:17:18.138 --> 00:17:19.007
You can go now.

315
00:17:19.139 --> 00:17:21.375
[light suspenseful music]

316
00:17:28.081 --> 00:17:28.983
[door closes]

317
00:17:29.617 --> 00:17:31.586
Can't stand that fucking guy.

318
00:17:32.286 --> 00:17:35.055
[woman on advertisement]
<i>Cold. Beer so cold...</i>

319
00:17:35.188 --> 00:17:37.759
[indistinct chatter
on advertisements]

320
00:17:51.104 --> 00:17:53.340
[engine whirring]

321
00:17:55.175 --> 00:17:56.811
[beeping]

322
00:18:01.916 --> 00:18:04.318
[shouting indistinctly]

323
00:18:07.522 --> 00:18:10.123
[electronic music playing]

324
00:18:16.496 --> 00:18:20.034
...like this one. I have
the perfect client for these.

325
00:18:20.167 --> 00:18:22.369
[indistinct chatter]

326
00:18:23.103 --> 00:18:26.541
Oh. look at this beast!

327
00:18:27.642 --> 00:18:28.776
Rail pistol.

328
00:18:29.209 --> 00:18:30.243
Gorgeous.

329
00:18:30.678 --> 00:18:32.647
Take off a lot of heads
with that one.

330
00:18:36.918 --> 00:18:38.151
Crilenger!

331
00:18:38.853 --> 00:18:39.988
Relax. boys.

332
00:18:40.454 --> 00:18:42.222
Aren't you worse for the wear?

333
00:18:42.991 --> 00:18:44.491
Still dashing. though.

334
00:18:46.060 --> 00:18:47.562
Something off the menu?

335
00:18:48.596 --> 00:18:51.699
The tiramisu? To die for.

336
00:18:51.833 --> 00:18:53.735
Tiramisu is overrated.

337
00:18:54.102 --> 00:18:56.269
Still using shock tips.

338
00:18:57.505 --> 00:18:58.940
Never kills anybody.

339
00:18:59.406 --> 00:19:01.542
Guy's a closet pacifist.

340
00:19:01.676 --> 00:19:04.244
[laughter]

341
00:19:05.312 --> 00:19:07.615
So. how'd it go?

342
00:19:07.749 --> 00:19:08.850
How do you think?

343
00:19:09.483 --> 00:19:11.853
The insider breached
the agreement.

344
00:19:12.252 --> 00:19:15.188
Why is this... my problem?

345
00:19:15.322 --> 00:19:16.456
You're the fixer.

346
00:19:16.891 --> 00:19:19.661
It's your responsibility
to vet these things.

347
00:19:20.227 --> 00:19:23.463
C... I adore you.

348
00:19:23.931 --> 00:19:27.135
But I warned you
from the get-go. the risks.

349
00:19:27.502 --> 00:19:29.236
That's why I offered
the insurance. but you said...

350
00:19:29.369 --> 00:19:31.438
[mockingly] "No. no. no!"

351
00:19:31.572 --> 00:19:33.107
[laughs]

352
00:19:33.240 --> 00:19:36.410
You take 15%.
That's insurance enough.

353
00:19:36.544 --> 00:19:38.880
-[Taa in normal voice]
We done here?
-[music continues playing]

354
00:19:39.013 --> 00:19:42.083
Really not into crying
over spilled lattes.

355
00:19:42.215 --> 00:19:43.751
but I do know a good therapist.

356
00:19:43.885 --> 00:19:45.318
[laughter]

357
00:19:45.452 --> 00:19:46.453
-[thud]
-[groans]

358
00:19:46.587 --> 00:19:47.555
-[grunts]
-[groans]

359
00:19:47.689 --> 00:19:49.189
-[bone crunches]
-[screams]

360
00:19:49.322 --> 00:19:51.859
-[gunshot]
-[clinking]

361
00:19:51.993 --> 00:19:53.828
[panting]

362
00:19:53.961 --> 00:19:56.964
I can hack your fucking data
in a heartbeat.

363
00:19:57.098 --> 00:19:59.701
I know a lot of folks
that would love to have access

364
00:19:59.834 --> 00:20:02.937
to those bank accounts
and your colorful home videos.

365
00:20:03.071 --> 00:20:05.338
Take it easy. for Christ's sake.

366
00:20:06.074 --> 00:20:10.243
Had no idea the corporate rat
was gonna be a problem.

367
00:20:10.377 --> 00:20:11.946
Who ordered the fix?

368
00:20:12.580 --> 00:20:14.816
If I break my confidentiality.

369
00:20:14.949 --> 00:20:17.585
you know what'll happen
to my reputation.

370
00:20:17.719 --> 00:20:21.189
Your reputation
is dropping fast.

371
00:20:21.923 --> 00:20:25.358
Fine. Can we just
let go. please?

372
00:20:25.492 --> 00:20:28.029
Let's figure this out.
like adults.

373
00:20:28.162 --> 00:20:30.397
[music continues playing]

374
00:20:31.699 --> 00:20:33.701
If you were anybody else.

375
00:20:33.835 --> 00:20:36.804
I'd personally remove your nuts
with a vegetable peeler.

376
00:20:37.505 --> 00:20:39.406
Christ.
you never lose your cool.

377
00:20:39.540 --> 00:20:42.210
This is different.
they breached the agreement.

378
00:20:42.342 --> 00:20:43.978
Have Ren take a look
at that hand.

379
00:20:44.712 --> 00:20:46.279
[Crilenger]
Give me a name. Taa.

380
00:20:46.413 --> 00:20:48.248
You know I can't do that.

381
00:20:49.550 --> 00:20:51.185
But I can give you a lead

382
00:20:51.318 --> 00:20:52.653
and a way to make
more money on this

383
00:20:52.787 --> 00:20:55.890
without upsetting
the order of things.

384
00:20:56.023 --> 00:20:57.424
I'm listening.

385
00:20:57.558 --> 00:21:00.661
The item the insider bagged.
Worth 50 times more

386
00:21:00.795 --> 00:21:02.630
than whatever your cut
was gonna be.

387
00:21:02.997 --> 00:21:06.968
-What is it?
-Some kind of bizarre
quantum processor.

388
00:21:07.101 --> 00:21:10.972
Opens the door to power.
Everlasting life. Whatever.

389
00:21:11.105 --> 00:21:14.075
You'd think they were talking
about the holy fucking grail.

390
00:21:14.208 --> 00:21:17.044
Apparently. a scientist
wants it. Pretty bad.

391
00:21:17.178 --> 00:21:19.981
-Who's the scientist?
-[Taa] A peculiar name.

392
00:21:20.848 --> 00:21:22.750
Dresden Corliss.

393
00:21:23.184 --> 00:21:26.888
I'll give you a location
and contact info on the buyer.
but that's it.

394
00:21:27.021 --> 00:21:30.290
I just want 5%
paid in the usual.

395
00:21:31.192 --> 00:21:32.927
-Sure.
-Good.

396
00:21:33.393 --> 00:21:35.730
Small warning.
though. sweetheart.

397
00:21:36.197 --> 00:21:37.632
People who call this in...

398
00:21:38.533 --> 00:21:41.434
[sing-songy]
...not ones to fuck with.

399
00:21:41.569 --> 00:21:43.805
[music continues playing]

400
00:21:46.507 --> 00:21:47.575
[in normal voice] Hey.

401
00:21:48.709 --> 00:21:50.845
I have a lot of overhead
runnin' this joint.

402
00:21:51.612 --> 00:21:53.446
Who's gonna cover
the medical bill?

403
00:21:55.650 --> 00:21:57.251
Don't you have insurance?

404
00:21:57.384 --> 00:21:58.653
[indistinct chatter]

405
00:21:58.786 --> 00:22:01.022
[light inspirational music]

406
00:22:01.421 --> 00:22:03.891
[Dresden]
<i>What is consciousness?</i>

407
00:22:05.293 --> 00:22:09.297
Is it primarily an electrical
and biochemical function

408
00:22:09.429 --> 00:22:11.065
of the neuronal
wiring of the brain

409
00:22:11.199 --> 00:22:13.935
sending funny little signals
to the body?

410
00:22:14.334 --> 00:22:16.804
"Eat. Move your arm. Duck!

411
00:22:16.938 --> 00:22:19.674
There's a Frisbee coming
towards your head!"
[chuckles softly]

412
00:22:20.508 --> 00:22:21.676
Adaptation.

413
00:22:22.176 --> 00:22:23.244
Survival.

414
00:22:23.878 --> 00:22:26.948
A genetic composition
telling us to do this.

415
00:22:27.081 --> 00:22:33.420
and then we choose
within those environmental
and biological precepts.

416
00:22:34.655 --> 00:22:36.057
That's a facet of it.

417
00:22:37.325 --> 00:22:42.330
But what is... this thing
we call consciousness?

418
00:22:43.197 --> 00:22:49.070
In ancient Sanskrit.
this is called <i>manas...</i>
or the mind.

419
00:22:49.737 --> 00:22:53.975
The philosophy breaks it
into two primary ideas.

420
00:22:54.508 --> 00:22:57.578
<i>Kama-manas.</i> or desire.

421
00:22:57.712 --> 00:23:00.514
such as survival. instinct.

422
00:23:00.648 --> 00:23:03.618
food. sex. ego.

423
00:23:04.185 --> 00:23:07.387
satisfying the state
of neuroplasticity

424
00:23:07.521 --> 00:23:09.257
that the brain has adapted to.

425
00:23:09.389 --> 00:23:11.592
Then. there's <i>Buddhi-manas.</i>

426
00:23:11.726 --> 00:23:14.996
-[music continues]
-Reason. logic...

427
00:23:16.063 --> 00:23:17.698
...cognitive processing.

428
00:23:17.832 --> 00:23:19.967
empathic perspectives.

429
00:23:20.601 --> 00:23:21.802
compassion!

430
00:23:23.204 --> 00:23:24.639
Perhaps telepathy.

431
00:23:25.373 --> 00:23:27.642
Our findings have revealed.

432
00:23:27.775 --> 00:23:29.442
on a quantum level.

433
00:23:29.577 --> 00:23:32.947
that consciousness.
or the enlightened mind.

434
00:23:33.446 --> 00:23:35.950
is as much
a byproduct of the brain

435
00:23:36.083 --> 00:23:41.622
as it is an individual
interdimensional construct

436
00:23:41.756 --> 00:23:43.456
of quantum energy.

437
00:23:43.958 --> 00:23:48.763
evolving and veering into
and out of organic material.

438
00:23:49.397 --> 00:23:52.600
What if we could prove
that consciousness...

439
00:23:53.401 --> 00:23:57.939
...or the soul.
if you wanna call it that...

440
00:23:58.973 --> 00:24:01.375
...decouples on a quantum level

441
00:24:01.776 --> 00:24:03.811
and reasserts itself

442
00:24:04.412 --> 00:24:07.615
in different form
beyond the body?

443
00:24:08.448 --> 00:24:09.684
Perhaps a new form...

444
00:24:10.918 --> 00:24:12.253
-...like reincarnation.
-[music continues]

445
00:24:12.386 --> 00:24:14.555
We have figured out
how to make the monocle

446
00:24:14.689 --> 00:24:19.360
extract memories. dreams.
energy from the brain.

447
00:24:19.727 --> 00:24:21.929
But what if it could go further?

448
00:24:22.330 --> 00:24:23.431
As they say.

449
00:24:23.998 --> 00:24:28.235
energy is neither
created nor destroyed.

450
00:24:28.369 --> 00:24:30.137
it simply transfers.

451
00:24:30.638 --> 00:24:33.874
And aren't we all just energy

452
00:24:34.008 --> 00:24:36.544
interacting and dancing together

453
00:24:36.677 --> 00:24:38.579
from one dimension to another?

454
00:24:39.146 --> 00:24:43.184
From one cosmological
ecosystem to another?

455
00:24:43.684 --> 00:24:44.785
[chuckles softly]

456
00:24:46.153 --> 00:24:47.121
Possibly.

457
00:24:49.623 --> 00:24:50.825
Maybe.

458
00:24:58.432 --> 00:25:00.668
[light melancholic music]

459
00:25:09.410 --> 00:25:10.878
-[soft sloshing]
-[pop]

460
00:25:12.446 --> 00:25:13.881
[soft pouring]

461
00:25:15.683 --> 00:25:16.951
[exhales deeply]

462
00:25:19.920 --> 00:25:22.023
[loudly gulps. exhales]

463
00:25:36.070 --> 00:25:37.071
[beeps]

464
00:25:48.482 --> 00:25:50.151
[inaudible chatter]

465
00:25:50.284 --> 00:25:52.319
[music continues]

466
00:26:07.168 --> 00:26:08.636
[sniffles]

467
00:26:13.874 --> 00:26:16.511
-[automated voice] <i>Caller ID.</i>
<i>Counselor Brightmore.</i>
-[beeping]

468
00:26:16.644 --> 00:26:19.246
[Brightmore]
<i>Doctor. how's</i>
<i>the retrofit coming?</i>

469
00:26:19.847 --> 00:26:22.249
[sighing] Uh. we're.
uh. we're working on it.

470
00:26:22.983 --> 00:26:24.685
The blueprint design you gave us

471
00:26:24.819 --> 00:26:27.054
is really challenging
to work with.

472
00:26:27.188 --> 00:26:28.823
um. but it's...

473
00:26:28.956 --> 00:26:31.092
<i>Exactly what</i>
<i>you were hoping for.</i>

474
00:26:31.560 --> 00:26:32.693
It's remarkable.

475
00:26:33.227 --> 00:26:36.030
The engineering.
I-- I've never seen
anything like it.

476
00:26:36.531 --> 00:26:38.966
When will we be able to see
the actual component?

477
00:26:39.100 --> 00:26:42.069
<i>There was a minor delay.</i>
<i>but you are getting the item.</i>

478
00:26:42.203 --> 00:26:44.238
<i>A courier will drop it off</i>
<i>soon enough.</i>

479
00:26:44.371 --> 00:26:47.041
-They stressed the timeline.
<i>-The Collective's aware.</i>

480
00:26:47.475 --> 00:26:49.677
<i>Use the account</i>
<i>we gave you to pay for it.</i>

481
00:26:50.144 --> 00:26:53.013
<i>You okay? You look spent.</i>

482
00:26:53.147 --> 00:26:55.783
[scoffs] I'm fine. really.

483
00:26:56.183 --> 00:26:59.720
-I saw the news about Peredor.
<i>-We had nothing to do with that.</i>

484
00:26:59.854 --> 00:27:01.556
-[suspenseful music]
-I'm not an idiot.

485
00:27:01.689 --> 00:27:03.157
<i>Nobody said you were.</i>

486
00:27:03.290 --> 00:27:06.227
Even if that's the case.
and I'm not saying it is...

487
00:27:07.194 --> 00:27:10.097
...couldn't that backfire on us?

488
00:27:10.532 --> 00:27:11.899
<i>Try not to worry about it.</i>

489
00:27:12.601 --> 00:27:14.268
<i>-Closing out.</i>
-[beeps]

490
00:27:16.003 --> 00:27:17.972
-[sighs]
-[alarm blaring]

491
00:27:18.105 --> 00:27:21.308
-[automated voice] <i>Attention...</i>
[continues indistinctly]
-[thunder rumbling]

492
00:27:21.442 --> 00:27:23.677
[rain spattering]

493
00:27:26.347 --> 00:27:28.382
[keyboard clacking]

494
00:27:30.651 --> 00:27:31.819
What the hell?

495
00:27:34.589 --> 00:27:36.991
[soft scratching]

496
00:27:39.528 --> 00:27:42.129
[automated voice speaking
