[engine rumbling]

737
00:40:00.935 --> 00:40:03.170
-[Ross] Just drop me off here.
-[birds chirping]

738
00:40:04.071 --> 00:40:04.839
[seat belt clicks]

739
00:40:04.972 --> 00:40:07.174
-[softly] Okay.
-[groans]

740
00:40:07.875 --> 00:40:08.876
[grunts]

741
00:40:13.281 --> 00:40:14.481
Uh. use these.

742
00:40:18.986 --> 00:40:20.521
[Ethan]
I can't see shit.

743
00:40:20.655 --> 00:40:22.790
The. uh. focus is
on the top. right here.

744
00:40:22.924 --> 00:40:24.592
-Ah.
-Yeah. yeah. yeah.

745
00:40:27.595 --> 00:40:31.565
-It's gonna be fine.
Two Musketeers.
-This seems like a bad idea.

746
00:40:32.967 --> 00:40:34.602
-Let's go.
-See you in a sec.

747
00:40:35.536 --> 00:40:36.771
[sighs]

748
00:40:38.339 --> 00:40:40.574
[birds chirping]

749
00:40:42.310 --> 00:40:43.544
[seat belt clicks]

750
00:40:45.680 --> 00:40:46.814
[grunts softly]

751
00:41:04.665 --> 00:41:05.766
So...

752
00:41:07.234 --> 00:41:10.538
...I believe
in a block universe.

753
00:41:11.772 --> 00:41:15.475
Like... [stutters softly]
there's a reason for everything.

754
00:41:16.344 --> 00:41:21.182
Electric particles...
dancing in some parabola.

755
00:41:22.316 --> 00:41:24.819
Stardust collecting
in an avalanche

756
00:41:24.952 --> 00:41:28.155
manifesting
this godforsaken rock.

757
00:41:29.290 --> 00:41:30.524
Cause...

758
00:41:31.726 --> 00:41:32.893
...and effect.

759
00:41:33.661 --> 00:41:35.495
Which leads me to a question.

760
00:41:36.364 --> 00:41:37.865
About actions. Ross.

761
00:41:37.999 --> 00:41:39.200
What ar--
what are you talking about?

762
00:41:39.333 --> 00:41:41.802
Crilenger and Z
managed to fly the coop.

763
00:41:41.936 --> 00:41:43.270
No. that's impossible.

764
00:41:43.704 --> 00:41:45.406
Crilenger's kinda special.

765
00:41:45.973 --> 00:41:47.942
Not a good loose end to have.

766
00:41:48.409 --> 00:41:50.111
Do you wanna keep
pontificating about karma.

767
00:41:50.244 --> 00:41:52.546
-or should we...
-Let's fucking see it.

768
00:41:52.680 --> 00:41:56.117
-Money first.
-Oh. no. no. no. no. no.

769
00:41:56.250 --> 00:41:58.652
I mean. I have
to justify the expense.

770
00:41:59.687 --> 00:42:04.525
The deal was to frame the mercs
<i>and</i> deliver the item.

771
00:42:05.526 --> 00:42:07.061
Why pay for both
when I only get one?

772
00:42:07.194 --> 00:42:08.863
Because I did
everything that you asked!

773
00:42:08.996 --> 00:42:11.432
-Half. Ross.
-That is bullshit!

774
00:42:11.565 --> 00:42:12.833
[Malik]
No!

775
00:42:13.200 --> 00:42:14.301
It's math.

776
00:42:15.102 --> 00:42:17.204
Give him the goddamn box. Ross.

777
00:42:17.738 --> 00:42:18.839
Yeah.

778
00:42:21.175 --> 00:42:22.076
I'm sorry.

779
00:42:22.710 --> 00:42:23.878
[sniffs] No.

780
00:42:25.646 --> 00:42:26.981
<i>I'm</i> sorry.

781
00:42:27.114 --> 00:42:29.518
I'm just fucking sorry
I hired a sales prick

782
00:42:29.650 --> 00:42:31.118
to do an ops job.

783
00:42:34.388 --> 00:42:35.990
Let's fucking see it.

784
00:42:37.191 --> 00:42:38.092
Money.

785
00:42:38.659 --> 00:42:41.629
Agent Claymore.
The case. please.

786
00:42:42.296 --> 00:42:43.197
[clicks]

787
00:42:46.567 --> 00:42:47.501
Wh-- uh-uh!

788
00:42:48.002 --> 00:42:50.004
[inhales sharply] No touching.

789
00:42:51.238 --> 00:42:53.808
[clicking]

790
00:43:01.115 --> 00:43:03.350
-[Malik sniffs]
-[keyboard clacking]

791
00:43:06.921 --> 00:43:09.323
[ominous music]

792
00:43:10.424 --> 00:43:11.358
Looks good.

793
00:43:11.492 --> 00:43:13.928
[inhales loudly] All right.

794
00:43:22.636 --> 00:43:23.771
Can I go?

795
00:43:23.904 --> 00:43:25.306
Absolutely.

796
00:43:26.307 --> 00:43:28.409
[music increases]

797
00:43:28.543 --> 00:43:29.877
[chuckles]

798
00:43:32.379 --> 00:43:33.347
[gunshot]

799
00:43:33.481 --> 00:43:34.381
[gasps]

800
00:43:34.516 --> 00:43:36.750
[soft splashing]

801
00:43:46.026 --> 00:43:47.328
-[weakly] Mom.
-[gun cocks]

802
00:43:47.461 --> 00:43:48.362
[gunshot]

803
00:43:48.762 --> 00:43:50.064
[gasps loudly and groans]

804
00:43:50.197 --> 00:43:52.333
-[shakily] No.
-Boss. we've got a problem.

805
00:43:53.167 --> 00:43:55.436
It's a. uh. display model.

806
00:43:56.370 --> 00:43:59.974
-[Malik] What?
-A good one. Fooled the program.
I went to double-check...

807
00:44:00.107 --> 00:44:02.309
-[shouts] He's fucking dead!
-...and. uh--

808
00:44:02.877 --> 00:44:06.647
You said straight up
that the scan would work!

809
00:44:07.815 --> 00:44:11.986
-I know. But the program...
[continues indistinctly]
-[Malik] Uh. shut the fuck up!

810
00:44:13.687 --> 00:44:15.322
[breathes shakily]

811
00:44:18.425 --> 00:44:20.094
[shouting]

812
00:44:20.227 --> 00:44:21.262
[gunshot]

813
00:44:22.263 --> 00:44:25.099
[softly]
Don't let that happen again.

814
00:44:26.000 --> 00:44:27.468
[softly] Yes. sir. I'm sorry.

815
00:44:27.602 --> 00:44:29.270
[engine starts]

816
00:44:29.937 --> 00:44:32.339
-[engine revving]
-[tires screeching]

817
00:44:32.907 --> 00:44:35.109
[gunshots]

818
00:44:37.778 --> 00:44:40.114
[whispers] Shit.
[loudly] You get the make?

819
00:44:40.247 --> 00:44:41.148
A4.

820
00:44:41.583 --> 00:44:42.783
Find out who owns it.

821
00:44:43.384 --> 00:44:44.885
-Clean up the mess.
-[Morris] Will do.

822
00:44:45.019 --> 00:44:47.788
[melancholic music]

823
00:44:48.355 --> 00:44:51.091
[birds squawking]

824
00:45:16.717 --> 00:45:17.952
[sniffles softly]

825
00:45:21.956 --> 00:45:24.058
[automated voice on PA]
<i>Silencia Police</i>
<i>Department parking...</i>

826
00:45:24.191 --> 00:45:25.459
[Ethan]
<i>And then. they. uh...</i>

827
00:45:25.594 --> 00:45:27.895
-[siren blaring in the distance]
-[horns honking]

828
00:45:28.796 --> 00:45:30.130
[shakily] then they shot him.

829
00:45:30.264 --> 00:45:32.199
What'd you say
the name of the assailant was?

830
00:45:32.601 --> 00:45:36.036
-The what?
-You mentioned
your friend was meeting someone.

831
00:45:36.571 --> 00:45:38.105
His name was Malik.

832
00:45:41.610 --> 00:45:44.646
[detective]
Wait here a minute.
I'm gonna make a few calls.

833
00:45:44.778 --> 00:45:48.115
-Fill out that form.
I'll be right back.
-[softly] All right.

834
00:45:49.016 --> 00:45:50.251
[door opens]

835
00:45:50.918 --> 00:45:51.752
[door closes]

836
00:45:51.885 --> 00:45:53.821
[soft scratching]

837
00:46:05.734 --> 00:46:08.269
[paper rustles]

838
00:46:19.246 --> 00:46:21.482
-[clatters]
-[suspenseful music]

839
00:46:24.586 --> 00:46:25.486
[door opens]

840
00:46:26.621 --> 00:46:27.522
[door closes]

841
00:46:30.791 --> 00:46:31.959
You okay?

842
00:46:32.594 --> 00:46:34.128
Yeah. um...

843
00:46:34.995 --> 00:46:36.564
...do you have another pen?

844
00:46:37.031 --> 00:46:38.365
This one's out of ink.

845
00:46:39.734 --> 00:46:40.968
Sure.

846
00:46:42.637 --> 00:46:43.605
Thank you.

847
00:46:43.738 --> 00:46:46.473
So... I checked with dispatch.

848
00:46:46.608 --> 00:46:48.610
several other patrols.

849
00:46:49.143 --> 00:46:51.613
No reports of the type
of activity you're describing.

850
00:46:51.746 --> 00:46:53.914
Okay. but I'm.
I'm telling you what happened.

851
00:46:58.886 --> 00:47:00.054
[softly] Off the record.

852
00:47:00.187 --> 00:47:02.657
That name you mentioned? Malik.

853
00:47:03.090 --> 00:47:04.091
Not a nice guy.

854
00:47:04.726 --> 00:47:07.928
If you could give me
just a little insight.

855
00:47:08.062 --> 00:47:10.565
I could alleviate
a lot of your problems.

856
00:47:11.332 --> 00:47:13.334
Wha-- what do you mean.
"insight"?

857
00:47:13.735 --> 00:47:15.869
Did your friend have
some kind of device?

858
00:47:16.236 --> 00:47:19.073
Special kinda processor. maybe?

859
00:47:19.973 --> 00:47:22.109
No. not. not.
not that I know of.

860
00:47:22.242 --> 00:47:23.444
You're sure about that?

861
00:47:24.411 --> 00:47:25.012
Yes.

862
00:47:25.145 --> 00:47:27.181
[music continues]

863
00:47:27.314 --> 00:47:29.983
All right.
File those reports then.

864
00:47:30.652 --> 00:47:32.486
[siren blaring]

865
00:47:32.620 --> 00:47:34.589
[automated voice on PA]
<i>Silencia Police</i>
<i>Department parking...</i>

866
00:47:34.723 --> 00:47:37.659
-Hey. pal.
<i>-...is reserved</i>
<i>for SPD employees only.</i>

867
00:47:37.792 --> 00:47:41.796
-[speaks indistinctly]
<i>-Any violation of SPD parking</i>

868
00:47:41.929 --> 00:47:43.430
<i>-will be met with deadly force.</i>
-Get in.

869
00:47:43.565 --> 00:47:46.066
-[grunting]
<i>-No exceptions.</i>

870
00:47:46.500 --> 00:47:49.937
<i>Thank you for choosing</i>
<i>Silencia Police Department</i>

871
00:47:50.070 --> 00:47:51.939
<i>for your safety and security.</i>

872
00:47:52.072 --> 00:47:53.307
[engine revving]

873
00:47:53.440 --> 00:47:55.309
Hey. don't fucking touch me.
asshole!

874
00:47:55.442 --> 00:47:57.512
-[thud]
-[Ethan groans]

875
00:47:58.078 --> 00:47:59.413
Breathe slow.

876
00:48:00.180 --> 00:48:01.382
Nice and slow.

877
00:48:01.783 --> 00:48:02.817
It'll come back.

878
00:48:02.950 --> 00:48:05.754
[breathes deeply and loudly]

879
00:48:05.886 --> 00:48:08.889
-[thud]
-[Ethan groans] Fuck!

880
00:48:09.022 --> 00:48:11.860
Yeah. Those ones really suck.

881
00:48:11.992 --> 00:48:14.061
What do you want? [panting]

882
00:48:14.194 --> 00:48:15.963
[Malik]
Just wanna know where it is.

883
00:48:17.030 --> 00:48:19.366
-What?
-[grunting]

884
00:48:19.500 --> 00:48:21.368
-[groans]
-[Malik] Tell us
where your little buddy

885
00:48:21.502 --> 00:48:24.806
-stashed his shit.
-I don't know! [panting]

886
00:48:24.938 --> 00:48:28.576
He just wanted me to drive him
to your goddamn meeting. okay?

887
00:48:29.878 --> 00:48:31.245
[exhales deeply]

888
00:48:31.780 --> 00:48:33.280
[softly and shakily] Please.

889
00:48:34.248 --> 00:48:35.449
-[grunts]
-[thud]

890
00:48:36.684 --> 00:48:38.887
[Ethan crying]

891
00:48:39.286 --> 00:48:41.523
-[sobs]
-[music continues]

892
00:48:42.423 --> 00:48:44.258
You killed my best friend.

893
00:48:45.426 --> 00:48:46.326
Your f--

894
00:48:46.895 --> 00:48:49.564
That guy was a fucking rat.

895
00:48:49.697 --> 00:48:51.833
What difference
does it make? Hmm?

896
00:48:52.567 --> 00:48:55.002
Even if I tell you...
[shakily breathes]

897
00:48:55.135 --> 00:48:56.638
...you'll just kill me anyway.

898
00:48:56.771 --> 00:48:59.641
Yeah. No. You're right. but...

899
00:49:01.643 --> 00:49:02.677
...but. you see...

900
00:49:04.077 --> 00:49:05.345
...I'll kill ya...

901
00:49:06.146 --> 00:49:07.882
...after we put you in the pit.

902
00:49:08.315 --> 00:49:10.484
We'll get the intel
out of you first...

903
00:49:11.251 --> 00:49:13.387
...and then you'll beg
for a quick death.

904
00:49:14.955 --> 00:49:16.223
Go fuck yourself.

905
00:49:17.357 --> 00:49:19.326
Saucy little motherfucker.

906
00:49:21.061 --> 00:49:22.996
[engines rumbling]

907
00:49:23.130 --> 00:49:25.533
[music continues]

908
00:49:31.506 --> 00:49:33.708
[birds chirping]

909
00:49:38.613 --> 00:49:40.615
-[engine rumbling loudly]
-[tires screeching]

910
00:49:41.850 --> 00:49:44.184
The motherfucking monk.

911
00:49:44.819 --> 00:49:46.386
[tires screeching]

912
00:49:46.521 --> 00:49:47.387
Don't move.

913
00:49:47.522 --> 00:49:49.591
[dramatic music]

914
00:49:49.724 --> 00:49:52.292
[gunshots]

915
00:49:53.160 --> 00:49:54.261
Move.

916
00:50:00.535 --> 00:50:01.636
-[crackling]
-[thudding]

917
00:50:06.173 --> 00:50:07.341
[thudding]

918
00:50:14.181 --> 00:50:15.315
[Malik]
Get him!

919
00:50:33.500 --> 00:50:35.603
[shouting]
Is that Zen enough for ya?

920
00:50:35.970 --> 00:50:37.872
Couldn't hack it in the agency.

921
00:50:38.006 --> 00:50:39.841
and ya can't hack it out here!

922
00:50:39.974 --> 00:50:43.176
Just never had the stomach
for it. did ya?

923
00:50:43.611 --> 00:50:46.179
-[gunshots continue]
-[gun clicks]

924
00:50:47.047 --> 00:50:49.283
[music continues]

925
00:50:50.652 --> 00:50:51.619
[gunshots]

926
00:50:52.452 --> 00:50:53.420
[grunts]

927
00:50:54.488 --> 00:50:55.422
[panting]

928
00:50:55.557 --> 00:50:57.324
-[grunts]
-[guns clatter]

929
00:51:01.663 --> 00:51:02.664
[shouts]

930
00:51:02.797 --> 00:51:03.865
-[gunshot]
-[gasps]

931
00:51:03.998 --> 00:51:04.999
-[groaning]
-[thudding]

932
00:51:05.132 --> 00:51:07.367
[gunshots]

933
00:51:09.637 --> 00:51:10.838
-[gunshot]
-[screams]

934
00:51:11.305 --> 00:51:13.541
-[grunting]
-[groaning]

935
00:51:14.576 --> 00:51:17.512
-[thudding]
-[yelling]

936
00:51:18.211 --> 00:51:19.413
[grunts]

937
00:51:24.052 --> 00:51:25.252
-[gun cocks]
-[exhales]

938
00:51:25.385 --> 00:51:28.623
[grunting and groaning continue]

939
00:51:30.525 --> 00:51:31.693
-[gunshot]
-[yells]

940
00:51:31.826 --> 00:51:33.728
[high-pitched ringing]

941
00:51:35.262 --> 00:51:37.497
[grunting]

942
00:51:41.501 --> 00:51:42.837
-[Malik] Oh. yeah.
-[grunting]

943
00:51:44.204 --> 00:51:45.640
-[gun cocks]
-[shouts] Hey!

944
00:51:45.773 --> 00:51:47.174
[gunshot]

945
00:51:47.307 --> 00:51:48.543
[shouts] Z. no!

946
00:51:48.676 --> 00:51:49.777
[gun cocks]

947
00:51:50.143 --> 00:51:51.311
Stop!

948
00:51:52.379 --> 00:51:54.247
-[gunshot]
-Goddamn it. Z!

949
00:51:55.415 --> 00:51:58.052
-[breathes shakily]
-What the fuck did I say?

950
00:51:58.185 --> 00:52:00.622
[panting]
I ran out of shock tips.

951
00:52:00.755 --> 00:52:03.791
Who cares? The guy is
a piece of... [screams] shit!

952
00:52:03.925 --> 00:52:05.292
[panting]

953
00:52:05.425 --> 00:52:07.061
-[Z exhales softly]
-You're missing the point.

954
00:52:07.194 --> 00:52:09.429
[siren blaring in the distance]

955
00:52:09.564 --> 00:52:11.331
He almost killed you.

956
00:52:13.001 --> 00:52:14.501
Do you wanna be like him?

957
00:52:16.203 --> 00:52:17.471
-[gun rattles]
-[softly] No.

958
00:52:19.206 --> 00:52:20.207
Sorry.

959
00:52:20.340 --> 00:52:21.475
Don't be.

960
00:52:22.409 --> 00:52:24.177
Thank you for saving my life.

961
00:52:27.882 --> 00:52:29.216
Are you okay?

962
00:52:29.349 --> 00:52:31.886
Yeah. I'll make it.
What happened to Mason?

963
00:52:32.787 --> 00:52:33.788
He took off.

964
00:52:35.056 --> 00:52:36.724
Oh. he's a sitting duck.

965
00:52:36.858 --> 00:52:39.727
He's probably heading
to the last place
he should be going.

966
00:52:40.327 --> 00:52:41.929
-[sighs]
-[Crilenger groans]

967
00:52:44.197 --> 00:52:45.733
-[grunts. sighs]
-[rattling]

968
00:52:47.568 --> 00:52:49.671
[siren blaring in the distance]

969
00:52:49.804 --> 00:52:52.406
-[suspenseful music]
-[whirring]

970
00:52:53.074 --> 00:52:54.609
-All right. Doc.
-[beeps]

971
00:53:00.581 --> 00:53:02.817
Javelin. you sent a team
out to his apartment. right?

972
00:53:02.950 --> 00:53:05.119
-Yep. Searching it now.
-[soft rattling]

973
00:53:05.252 --> 00:53:07.055
Oh. found him.

974
00:53:07.522 --> 00:53:09.624
He's about three clicks away
on G Street.

975
00:53:09.757 --> 00:53:12.192
-heading... north.
-[keyboard clacking]

976
00:53:13.061 --> 00:53:14.529
[sighs] Where does he work?

977
00:53:14.962 --> 00:53:16.430
Mutual One Investments.

978
00:53:17.098 --> 00:53:18.599
Jack Wellman.

979
00:53:18.733 --> 00:53:19.801
Familiar?

980
00:53:19.934 --> 00:53:21.468
Hoity-toity prick.

981
00:53:22.003 --> 00:53:24.204
Took out his rivals for him
a few years back

982
00:53:24.337 --> 00:53:26.174
during that shit show
in The Centrals.

983
00:53:26.306 --> 00:53:27.175
[grunts]

984
00:53:27.742 --> 00:53:29.844
So. if we don't get
the kid at his pad...

985
00:53:31.145 --> 00:53:32.613
...go to Mutual One.

986
00:53:36.184 --> 00:53:38.019
[gulps and sighs]

987
00:53:38.152 --> 00:53:39.887
[somber music]

988
00:53:40.021 --> 00:53:43.958
-[explosions]
-[helicopter blades whirring]

989
00:53:57.437 --> 00:53:58.438
[fire crackling in the distance]

990
00:53:58.573 --> 00:53:59.974
No witnesses.

991
00:54:03.745 --> 00:54:04.846
[Crilenger]
I won't.

992
00:54:06.346 --> 00:54:09.817
Do it.
