01:07:30.885 --> 01:07:32.052
[whooshing]

1244
01:07:32.185 --> 01:07:34.488
-[gunshot echoes]
-[gasps and grunts]

1245
01:07:37.291 --> 01:07:38.826
-[inaudible chatter on PC]
-[Ethan sighs]

1246
01:07:38.960 --> 01:07:41.128
-[Z] Is that from--
-From Corliss's lecture.

1247
01:07:41.261 --> 01:07:42.329
[Ethan grunts]

1248
01:07:42.931 --> 01:07:46.000
Yeah. some concepts she designed
about particle transference.

1249
01:07:46.366 --> 01:07:47.535
Uh. how much further?

1250
01:07:48.201 --> 01:07:49.369
About 50 clicks.

1251
01:07:49.503 --> 01:07:51.706
[somber. suspenseful music]

1252
01:07:52.105 --> 01:07:53.340
[grunts]

1253
01:07:54.207 --> 01:07:55.543
You know. I was wondering...

1254
01:07:57.110 --> 01:08:00.247
...you guys don't kill anybody?
I mean. you are mercs. right?

1255
01:08:00.615 --> 01:08:02.382
Crilenger's got a different...

1256
01:08:03.417 --> 01:08:05.218
...philosophy to all that.

1257
01:08:05.587 --> 01:08:07.187
Why do you work for Wellman?

1258
01:08:09.323 --> 01:08:13.561
Good with... numbers
and patterns. I guess.

1259
01:08:13.962 --> 01:08:15.095
It's just a job.

1260
01:08:16.064 --> 01:08:17.364
Just a job.

1261
01:08:18.398 --> 01:08:20.300
[clicks tongue] Okay.

1262
01:08:21.501 --> 01:08:23.037
I found some fraud
in the company.

1263
01:08:23.403 --> 01:08:24.606
How surprising.

1264
01:08:24.739 --> 01:08:25.840
[Ethan]
And they know about it.

1265
01:08:27.008 --> 01:08:28.108
I told them.

1266
01:08:28.676 --> 01:08:29.644
That was dumb.

1267
01:08:29.777 --> 01:08:31.411
They're the ones
that asked me to look.

1268
01:08:31.546 --> 01:08:34.247
And you're getting worked.
office boy.

1269
01:08:34.381 --> 01:08:36.283
You know.
I don't even like offices.

1270
01:08:37.552 --> 01:08:39.587
It's funny. though.
my dad didn't seem to mind.

1271
01:08:40.655 --> 01:08:42.189
The guy was obsessed with money.

1272
01:08:42.824 --> 01:08:45.325
Keeping up
with the Joneses. [laughs]

1273
01:08:45.827 --> 01:08:48.362
-Always stressed.
-[music continues]

1274
01:08:48.495 --> 01:08:50.430
Took it out on us
all the time too.

1275
01:08:51.131 --> 01:08:52.165
Then he did some deal.

1276
01:08:52.700 --> 01:08:55.268
Lost a bunch of money
for a mutual fund company.

1277
01:08:55.402 --> 01:08:57.005
and the SEC
threatened jail time.

1278
01:08:57.137 --> 01:08:58.438
He get convicted?

1279
01:08:58.906 --> 01:08:59.807
[Ethan]
No.

1280
01:09:00.240 --> 01:09:01.208
He killed himself.

1281
01:09:01.341 --> 01:09:03.143
[exhales shakily] That's brutal.

1282
01:09:03.276 --> 01:09:06.614
Yeah. My mom got
real depressed after that.

1283
01:09:07.715 --> 01:09:09.383
OD'd on some benzos
shortly after.

1284
01:09:09.517 --> 01:09:13.554
I was about 12...
or something at the time.

1285
01:09:15.155 --> 01:09:16.490
Both parents.

1286
01:09:17.290 --> 01:09:18.392
[Ethan]
Yeah.

1287
01:09:19.393 --> 01:09:20.293
[whispers] Fuck.

1288
01:09:20.695 --> 01:09:22.362
[Ethan]
But it got me thinking.

1289
01:09:23.263 --> 01:09:24.832
Why was he so miserable?

1290
01:09:26.701 --> 01:09:28.335
'Cause it wasn't
just his choices.

1291
01:09:29.070 --> 01:09:31.906
Have you heard of the term
"structural violence"?

1292
01:09:32.040 --> 01:09:32.974
No.

1293
01:09:33.440 --> 01:09:35.643
Negative externalities
of society.

1294
01:09:36.476 --> 01:09:39.479
Right? It could be
workplace stress

1295
01:09:39.881 --> 01:09:44.786
or. um. it could be...
poverty or pollution.

1296
01:09:45.419 --> 01:09:46.554
It affects everything.

1297
01:09:46.988 --> 01:09:49.557
In reality. our decisions
are defined by what is available

1298
01:09:49.924 --> 01:09:52.727
or by what we perceive
as available.

1299
01:09:52.860 --> 01:09:55.863
Even though
my father was the one
to pull the trigger...

1300
01:09:56.597 --> 01:10:00.034
...if the incentives
were different in any way.

1301
01:10:00.168 --> 01:10:01.836
his decision might've changed

1302
01:10:01.969 --> 01:10:04.539
-and he might
still be here today.
-[music continues]

1303
01:10:04.672 --> 01:10:07.041
It's actually why I got
into architectural engineering.

1304
01:10:07.742 --> 01:10:09.610
Better living through design.

1305
01:10:10.210 --> 01:10:11.411
[Ethan]
Exactly!

1306
01:10:11.879 --> 01:10:12.914
Free energy.

1307
01:10:13.881 --> 01:10:15.282
Smart production.

1308
01:10:15.415 --> 01:10:16.784
Stress-free aesthetics.

1309
01:10:16.918 --> 01:10:18.886
We could live in a world
of zero marginal cost

1310
01:10:19.020 --> 01:10:23.191
if we just changed
how we designed
our way of building things.

1311
01:10:23.658 --> 01:10:25.325
It's better
than fucking up the planet.

1312
01:10:25.760 --> 01:10:27.995
You hear that. Z?
We have another idealist.

1313
01:10:28.129 --> 01:10:29.229
[Z]
Mm-hmm.

1314
01:10:29.362 --> 01:10:31.199
No. it's just logical.

1315
01:10:31.331 --> 01:10:32.332
Yeah.

1316
01:10:32.767 --> 01:10:35.837
As if the corps
will ever let that happen.

1317
01:10:35.970 --> 01:10:37.304
Change is coming.

1318
01:10:39.574 --> 01:10:41.676
Did you slip something
into Crilenger's coffee?

1319
01:10:41.809 --> 01:10:42.810
[chuckles]

1320
01:10:43.578 --> 01:10:45.079
It's stupid. yeah.

1321
01:10:45.213 --> 01:10:46.614
"If you do not change direction.

1322
01:10:46.748 --> 01:10:48.783
you end up where you're heading.

1323
01:10:50.283 --> 01:10:52.319
If I let go of what I am.

1324
01:10:52.452 --> 01:10:54.856
I might become what I might be."

1325
01:10:54.989 --> 01:10:55.890
Lao Tzu.

1326
01:10:56.724 --> 01:10:58.693
I know why
you're working for Wellman.

1327
01:10:58.826 --> 01:10:59.927
Yeah? Why?

1328
01:11:00.862 --> 01:11:01.696
Fear.

1329
01:11:01.829 --> 01:11:04.031
[music continues]

1330
01:11:04.165 --> 01:11:06.366
I'm sorry about Ross.

1331
01:11:06.934 --> 01:11:08.035
He was a good guy.

1332
01:11:09.837 --> 01:11:11.906
His family took me in after...

1333
01:11:12.974 --> 01:11:14.742
-He was just a little bit--
-Greedy.

1334
01:11:15.710 --> 01:11:17.645
Yeah. that's kinda par
for the course.

1335
01:11:18.345 --> 01:11:19.547
Yeah.

1336
01:11:21.048 --> 01:11:23.551
[clears throat]
So... [clears throat] your turn.

1337
01:11:27.021 --> 01:11:28.022
My turn?

1338
01:11:28.156 --> 01:11:30.825
What. why the no-kill policy?

1339
01:11:30.958 --> 01:11:31.859
Yeah.

1340
01:11:33.027 --> 01:11:35.362
-Maybe another time.
-[Ethan] Oh!

1341
01:11:36.130 --> 01:11:37.665
Well. that's not fair.

1342
01:11:38.733 --> 01:11:39.967
So. are we on an op?

1343
01:11:40.333 --> 01:11:42.537
No. we're not on an op.

1344
01:11:44.238 --> 01:11:45.606
We're cleaning up a mess.

1345
01:11:46.107 --> 01:11:47.975
-Well. that's a shame.
-[upbeat suspenseful music]

1346
01:11:48.109 --> 01:11:50.511
Kinda felt like we were
a team there for a second.

1347
01:11:50.645 --> 01:11:51.979
You know. I think I'm gonna
put on some talk radio.

1348
01:11:52.113 --> 01:11:54.447
I think
that's a fucking good idea.

1349
01:11:54.582 --> 01:11:56.717
-[keyboard clacking]
-[Morris] Okay. uh.

1350
01:11:56.851 --> 01:11:58.653
I managed to track
Ross's location

1351
01:11:58.786 --> 01:12:00.988
from the time you called him

1352
01:12:01.388 --> 01:12:03.191
and searched the vicinity.

1353
01:12:03.323 --> 01:12:06.359
-[keyboard clacking]
-[chiming]

1354
01:12:14.869 --> 01:12:17.672
Looks like the dog
wants to bury a bone.

1355
01:12:18.039 --> 01:12:20.808
This is about
the time we lost him.

1356
01:12:20.942 --> 01:12:22.442
but. I mean. there's nothing.

1357
01:12:22.944 --> 01:12:25.980
Zoom in on the taxi ID number
next to the plate.

1358
01:12:26.948 --> 01:12:28.082
[chiming]

1359
01:12:30.585 --> 01:12:32.687
It's. uh. 7:34 a.m.

1360
01:12:35.256 --> 01:12:37.758
So. what are you gonna do?

1361
01:12:37.892 --> 01:12:40.761
I'm gonna hack into their system
and find the routing assignment.

1362
01:12:40.895 --> 01:12:41.963
Attaboy.

1363
01:12:44.565 --> 01:12:46.834
-[whirring and beeping]
-[Morris] Oh. shit.

1364
01:12:46.968 --> 01:12:50.137
It's the RZ. there's no
satellite images out there.

1365
01:12:50.905 --> 01:12:52.840
Go back to Mason's apartment.

1366
01:12:52.974 --> 01:12:54.709
[music continues]

1367
01:12:54.842 --> 01:12:55.743
[chimes]

1368
01:12:58.346 --> 01:13:00.447
Crilenger's car. Next one.

1369
01:13:02.316 --> 01:13:03.217
[chimes]

1370
01:13:03.351 --> 01:13:04.886
Fuck. it's ghosted.

1371
01:13:05.019 --> 01:13:05.920
Doesn't matter.

1372
01:13:06.587 --> 01:13:07.922
We know where they're going.

1373
01:13:10.390 --> 01:13:12.660
[sniffs] Offering 100K.

1374
01:13:13.728 --> 01:13:16.864
Two males. one female.
one salvage. A hard case.

1375
01:13:16.998 --> 01:13:19.066
Approximately 30 minutes away
from your sector.

1376
01:13:19.200 --> 01:13:22.603
driving a black armored coupé.
Sending coordinates now.

1377
01:13:23.738 --> 01:13:25.840
-[snaps finger]
-[suspenseful music]

1378
01:13:25.973 --> 01:13:27.909
[wind blowing]

1379
01:13:28.042 --> 01:13:29.877
[engine rumbling]

1380
01:13:30.011 --> 01:13:32.046
[whirring]

1381
01:13:33.748 --> 01:13:35.082
I can't see shit.

1382
01:13:35.650 --> 01:13:36.984
I'm working on it. Z.

1383
01:13:42.556 --> 01:13:44.125
-[thudding and rumbling]
-Jesus!

1384
01:13:44.659 --> 01:13:46.294
Is it always like this out here?

1385
01:13:46.459 --> 01:13:47.628
It's just debris.

1386
01:13:47.762 --> 01:13:49.496
-[whirring and beeping]
-All right.

1387
01:13:49.630 --> 01:13:52.199
Z. three clicks. nine o'clock.

1388
01:13:52.333 --> 01:13:53.935
I fucking hate this place.

1389
01:13:56.304 --> 01:13:59.340
-[ominous music]
-[male collective 8]
<i>Malik's becoming a liability.</i>

1390
01:13:59.472 --> 01:14:01.876
<i>Termination and/or incarceration</i>

1391
01:14:02.009 --> 01:14:04.812
<i>of the associates</i>
<i>was not authorized.</i>

1392
01:14:05.445 --> 01:14:07.281
It was something he demanded
as part of the deal.

1393
01:14:07.415 --> 01:14:09.250
[female collective 3]
<i>These actions have elevated</i>

1394
01:14:09.383 --> 01:14:12.887
<i>unnecessary exposure.</i>
<i>Mutual One and Peredor</i>

1395
01:14:13.020 --> 01:14:15.423
<i>have already implicated</i>
<i>our involvement.</i>

1396
01:14:15.556 --> 01:14:18.491
[male collective 8]
<i>The operation would've been</i>
<i>more expedient</i>

1397
01:14:18.626 --> 01:14:20.127
<i>if he wasn't playing games</i>

1398
01:14:20.261 --> 01:14:22.363
<i>with the crew he assembled</i>
<i>through the fixer.</i>

1399
01:14:22.495 --> 01:14:25.900
<i>They are close</i>
<i>to the recovery of the sphere?</i>

1400
01:14:26.033 --> 01:14:28.602
-They are.
-[female collective 1]
<i>Malik must be focused</i>

1401
01:14:28.736 --> 01:14:30.237
<i>on the final phase.</i>

1402
01:14:30.371 --> 01:14:32.173
<i>Please remove him</i>
<i>from the current assignment.</i>

1403
01:14:32.306 --> 01:14:35.743
<i>We trust the freelancers</i>
<i>will complete the transaction.</i>

1404
01:14:35.876 --> 01:14:37.345
My pleasure. Collective.

1405
01:14:38.112 --> 01:14:40.715
What about Mutual One's
employee. Ethan Mason?

1406
01:14:40.848 --> 01:14:42.583
[male collective 8]
<i>We have a unique opportunity</i>

1407
01:14:42.717 --> 01:14:44.151
<i>with Mr. Mason.</i>

1408
01:14:44.285 --> 01:14:45.820
Are you suggesting
a test subject?

1409
01:14:45.953 --> 01:14:47.788
[female collective 5]
<i>Indeed.</i>

1410
01:14:48.189 --> 01:14:49.190
I'll look into it.

1411
01:14:49.757 --> 01:14:51.993
[engine rumbling]

1412
01:14:58.265 --> 01:15:00.401
-[high-pitched ringing]
-[distorted whooshing]

1413
01:15:00.534 --> 01:15:01.602
[beeping]

1414
01:15:01.736 --> 01:15:03.971
[wind blowing]

1415
01:15:05.506 --> 01:15:07.108
-[high-pitched ringing]
-[distorted whooshing]

1416
01:15:07.241 --> 01:15:08.509
[Z]
Fuck. it's cold!

1417
01:15:11.345 --> 01:15:12.780
[car doors close]

1418
01:15:12.913 --> 01:15:16.017
-[high-pitched ringing]
-[distorted whooshing]

1419
01:15:17.084 --> 01:15:18.953
What the hell
happened here. anyway?

1420
01:15:19.820 --> 01:15:20.921
-Pop version or the truth?
-[high-pitched ringing]

1421
01:15:21.055 --> 01:15:22.757
-[distorted whooshing]
-Truth?

1422
01:15:24.225 --> 01:15:26.260
Some quantum engineers
were brought in years ago

1423
01:15:26.394 --> 01:15:29.697
by DARPA to try to create
a multidimensional shift
in the region.

1424
01:15:29.830 --> 01:15:31.632
-[somber. ominous music]
-The idea was to do

1425
01:15:31.766 --> 01:15:33.367
some kind of
interdimensional surveillance

1426
01:15:33.501 --> 01:15:35.036
-using the fusion power.
-[high-pitched ringing]

1427
01:15:35.169 --> 01:15:37.671
-[distorted whooshing]
-But a rift happened.

1428
01:15:38.406 --> 01:15:40.474
Instead of being able
to spy in other dimensions.

1429
01:15:40.608 --> 01:15:43.244
-it affected the subatomic
structure of the area...
-[distorted whooshing]

1430
01:15:43.377 --> 01:15:45.046
...affecting the ecosystem.

1431
01:15:45.646 --> 01:15:47.615
Physics is different.
law is different.

1432
01:15:48.549 --> 01:15:51.986
The fragment that got through
affected the physics.

1433
01:15:52.853 --> 01:15:55.456
Climate.
weather affected mostly.

1434
01:15:55.589 --> 01:15:57.792
but also communication.

1435
01:15:58.225 --> 01:16:00.761
-[high-pitched ringing]
-[distorted whooshing]

1436
01:16:01.530 --> 01:16:03.097
They abandoned the project...

1437
01:16:03.898 --> 01:16:05.433
...and put a cover story on it.

1438
01:16:05.866 --> 01:16:08.302
-Wouldn't that affect
the rest of the world?
-[distorted whooshing]

1439
01:16:08.436 --> 01:16:09.904
You'd think so.

1440
01:16:10.037 --> 01:16:12.273
They managed to keep it
isolated for now. but who knows?

1441
01:16:12.406 --> 01:16:14.675
-[high-pitched ringing]
-[distorted whooshing]

1442
01:16:14.809 --> 01:16:17.078
A lot of strange shit
happens here.

1443
01:16:18.345 --> 01:16:21.282
-I'm guessing
this used to be a mining town?
-[distorted whooshing]

1444
01:16:21.415 --> 01:16:22.551
Yeah.

1445
01:16:23.250 --> 01:16:25.619
-Sacred burial ground
before that.
-[high-pitched ringing]

1446
01:16:25.753 --> 01:16:28.689
-[distorted whooshing]
-Before the dipshits
of DARPA fucked that up.

1447
01:16:28.823 --> 01:16:31.659
The locals like
to call it "Frankenland."

1448
01:16:32.860 --> 01:16:34.762
-[high-pitched ringing]
-[distorted whooshing]

1449
01:16:34.895 --> 01:16:37.131
[music continues]

1450
01:16:40.234 --> 01:16:43.070
-[high-pitched ringing]
-[distorted whooshing]

1451
01:16:43.204 --> 01:16:45.239
[wind blowing]

1452
01:16:47.509 --> 01:16:49.210
[distorted whooshing]

1453
01:16:50.411 --> 01:16:51.312
[buzzing]

1454
01:16:52.646 --> 01:16:55.049
-[loud bang]
-You guys okay?

1455
01:16:55.182 --> 01:16:57.184
-[softly] Yeah.
-[distorted whooshing]

1456
01:17:02.389 --> 01:17:03.757
[distorted whooshing]

1457
01:17:03.891 --> 01:17:06.660
[whirring and buzzing]

1458
01:17:08.496 --> 01:17:10.698
-[high-pitched ringing]
-[distorted whooshing]

1459
01:17:15.169 --> 01:17:16.270
[dropping]

1460
01:17:16.403 --> 01:17:17.938
[distorted whooshing]

1461
01:17:22.943 --> 01:17:25.212
-[high-pitched ringing]
-[distorted whooshing]

1462
01:17:26.313 --> 01:17:28.082
-[soft sloshing]
-[soft buzzing]

1463
01:17:31.051 --> 01:17:33.154
[distorted whooshing]

1464
01:17:34.388 --> 01:17:36.657
-[Crilenger] You guys okay?
-[Z softly] Yeah.

1465
01:17:36.790 --> 01:17:38.259
-[panting and grunting]
-[zips]

1466
01:17:38.392 --> 01:17:39.793
[Ethan]
I can't see anything.

1467
01:17:39.927 --> 01:17:41.095
[Crilenger grunting]
Hang on. [sniffs]

1468
01:17:41.228 --> 01:17:43.797
-[soft clattering]
-[sighs]

1469
01:17:43.931 --> 01:17:45.399
[exhales loudly] Okay.

1470
01:17:46.367 --> 01:17:47.368
[softly] All right.

1471
01:17:49.236 --> 01:17:51.405
Twenty-five meters.
twelve o'clock.

1472
01:17:52.339 --> 01:17:53.941
[exhales. sniffs]

1473
01:17:54.742 --> 01:17:58.679
[Crilenger breathing loudly]

1474
01:18:00.981 --> 01:18:03.284
[buzzing and whirring]

1475
01:18:03.417 --> 01:18:05.452
[suspenseful music]

1476
01:18:12.927 --> 01:18:14.428
Strange stuff.

1477
01:18:39.320 --> 01:18:40.354
It's here.

1478
01:18:47.294 --> 01:18:48.229
I'll dig.

1479
01:18:52.366 --> 01:18:53.234
[thud]

1480
01:18:53.367 --> 01:18:55.302
[engines rumbling]

1481
01:18:55.436 --> 01:18:57.471
[ominous music]

1482
01:19:09.416 --> 01:19:10.985
[engines revving]

1483
01:19:20.060 --> 01:19:21.395
-[high-pitched ringing]
-[distorted whooshing]

1484
01:19:26.934 --> 01:19:28.369
[distorted whooshing]

1485
01:19:29.436 --> 01:19:30.804
[gun cocks]

1486
01:19:32.773 --> 01:19:34.775
-[high-pitched ringing]
-[distorted whooshing]

1487
01:19:35.909 --> 01:19:36.977
[Ethan grunts]

1488
01:19:37.579 --> 01:19:39.514
[blows. grunts]

1489
01:19:39.648 --> 01:19:42.049
[suspenseful music]

1490
01:19:44.719 --> 01:19:45.819
Key.

1491
01:19:48.355 --> 01:19:49.256
Please?

1492
01:19:54.995 --> 01:19:58.232
-[clicking]
-[whirring]

1493
01:20:02.136 --> 01:20:04.905
-[clack]
-[clicking]

1494
01:20:07.308 --> 01:20:08.643
-C! [grunts]
-[shouts] What?

1495
01:20:08.777 --> 01:20:09.644
-[gunshots]
-[gasps]

1496
01:20:09.778 --> 01:20:10.844
[panting]

1497
01:20:10.978 --> 01:20:12.813
-[grunting]
-[Ethan] Z!

1498
01:20:12.946 --> 01:20:13.782
[Z]
Fuck!

1499
01:20:13.914 --> 01:20:16.350
[cell phone ringing]

1500
01:20:16.483 --> 01:20:18.753
-[beeps]
-Kind of in the middle.

1501
01:20:18.886 --> 01:20:20.120
[Brightmore]
<i>Call it off.</i>

1502
01:20:21.121 --> 01:20:23.957
-What the fuck?
<i>-Start prepping the next phase.</i>

1503
01:20:24.559 --> 01:20:27.294
But we're this close
to pulling it off!

1504
01:20:27.696 --> 01:20:29.029
<i>Collective's orders.</i>

1505
01:20:30.598 --> 01:20:31.965
[clattering]

1506
01:20:32.099 --> 01:20:33.967
[groaning] It hurts!

1507
01:20:34.401 --> 01:20:36.370
Ethan.
there's first aid in the bag.

1508
01:20:36.503 --> 01:20:37.971
There's an injection.
You can use it in the wound

1509
01:20:38.105 --> 01:20:39.774
to seal it up and disinfect it.

1510
01:20:39.907 --> 01:20:41.375
-Here. take this.
-[gun rattles]

1511
01:20:41.810 --> 01:20:43.812
-Remember what I told you.
-[Z breathes loudly]

1512
01:20:43.944 --> 01:20:45.479
[dramatic music]

1513
01:20:45.613 --> 01:20:48.550
-[Ethan whispers]
Let me take this off.
-[groaning]

1514
01:20:48.683 --> 01:20:50.417
[panting]

1515
01:20:52.453 --> 01:20:53.987
-[Z grunts]
-You ready?

1516
01:20:54.121 --> 01:20:55.422
Not really.

1517
01:20:55.557 --> 01:20:57.024
-[shouts] Fuck!
-[softly] Yeah.

1518
01:20:58.192 --> 01:21:00.327
-[distorted whooshing]
-[gunshots]

1519
01:21:00.461 --> 01:21:02.496
[music increases]

1520
01:21:04.666 --> 01:21:07.067
-[thudding]
-[distorted whooshing]

1521
01:21:10.003 --> 01:21:12.306
[high-pitched ringing]

1522
01:21:13.207 --> 01:21:14.576
[distorted whooshing]

1523
01:21:20.247 --> 01:21:21.448
[distorted whooshing]

1524
01:21:25.119 --> 01:21:26.654
[engine starts]

1525
01:21:27.087 --> 01:21:28.389
[distorted whooshing]

1526
01:21:30.224 --> 01:21:32.594
[engine rumbling]

1527
01:21:34.629 --> 01:21:37.030
-How you feeling?
-[breathes heavily] Better.

1528
01:21:37.599 --> 01:21:39.967
-[softly] Thanks.
-No. thank you.

1529
01:21:40.100 --> 01:21:42.002
If it weren't for you.
we'd be toast by now.

1530
01:21:42.403 --> 01:21:44.471
Keep your eyes peeled
and hand on the trigger.

1531
01:21:44.606 --> 01:21:45.607
Yes. ma'am.

1532
01:21:46.608 --> 01:21:48.543
[engines rumbling]

1533
01:21:48.676 --> 01:21:50.911
[dramatic music]

1534
01:22:20.974 --> 01:22:22.476
[distorted whooshing]

1535
01:22:24.913 --> 01:22:27.314
[engines revving]

1536
01:22:43.230 --> 01:22:45.733
-[high-pitched ringing]
-[distorted whooshing]

1537
01:22:47.267 --> 01:22:48.636
[soft sloshing]

1538
01:22:48.770 --> 01:22:50.572
[engine rumbling]

1539
01:22:50.705 --> 01:22:52.740
[music continues]

1540
01:23:02.584 --> 01:23:04.117
-[gunshot]
-[thudding]

1541
01:23:10.023 --> 01:23:13.427
At least the money
is still good.

1542
01:23:13.928 --> 01:23:17.064
Not everything's about
the money. Brokowski.

1543
01:23:25.038 --> 01:23:26.808
Abort the mission.

1544
01:23:27.174 --> 01:23:29.577
[on radio] <i>I repeat. abort...</i>

1545
01:23:30.110 --> 01:23:31.311
...the mission.

1546
01:23:39.019 --> 01:23:41.589
[clicks tongue] Oh. God.

1547
01:23:42.422 --> 01:23:44.224
I miss the tropics.

1548
01:23:47.962 --> 01:23:50.230
[breathing heavily]

1549
01:23:50.965 --> 01:23:52.099
[sighs]

1550
01:23:52.967 --> 01:23:54.368
What took you so long?

1551
01:23:54.903 --> 01:23:55.904
[pants]

1552
01:23:56.036 --> 01:23:57.972
[tense music]

1553
01:23:58.105 --> 01:24:00.542
Kerry. relax. Have a cream soda.

1554
01:24:00.675 --> 01:24:02.710
No. thanks. FYI.

1555
01:24:02.844 --> 01:24:04.779
Malik's contracted
with C & Earth.

1556
01:24:04.913 --> 01:24:06.179
See? I told you.

1557
01:24:06.313 --> 01:24:09.017
Relax. Tran.
Jesus Christ. what else?

1558
01:24:09.149 --> 01:24:10.652
They stole Peredor's tech.

1559
01:24:11.318 --> 01:24:12.854
The whole thing
was a bit of a fuck-up.

1560
01:24:13.253 --> 01:24:16.891
C & Earth hired Malik.
Malik got some insider
and hired a fixer

1561
01:24:17.025 --> 01:24:18.492
to assemble a couple of mercs.

1562
01:24:18.626 --> 01:24:20.528
They're delivering it
to someone at Aurora Limited.

1563
01:24:20.662 --> 01:24:22.764
It's one
of C & Earth's subsidiaries.

1564
01:24:22.897 --> 01:24:23.831
Who are the mercs?

1565
01:24:23.965 --> 01:24:26.099
Crilenger and Zephyr Gates.

1566
01:24:26.233 --> 01:24:28.135
The monk. [chuckles softly]

1567
01:24:28.770 --> 01:24:31.906
Let me guess. Malik was gonna
frame him for the job.

1568
01:24:32.040 --> 01:24:33.373
Something like that.

1569
01:24:33.975 --> 01:24:36.143
Crilenger's a unique brand.

1570
01:24:36.644 --> 01:24:37.845
Wasn't he agency?

1571
01:24:37.979 --> 01:24:39.179
Oh. yeah. counterintelligence.

1572
01:24:39.313 --> 01:24:41.214
He was the brightest star
they ever had.

1573
01:24:41.348 --> 01:24:43.551
[chuckles]
Sorry the son of a bitch quit.

1574
01:24:43.685 --> 01:24:44.619
What's the plan?

1575
01:24:45.753 --> 01:24:47.087
Recover the tech.

1576
01:24:47.655 --> 01:24:48.623
What about Malik?

1577
01:24:50.758 --> 01:24:52.060
Zero his ass.

1578
01:24:52.627 --> 01:24:54.194
[woman on advertisement]
<i>The Grinder.</i>

1579
01:24:54.328 --> 01:24:56.598
<i>this hard and hot</i>
<i>fiery thick one...</i>

1580
01:24:56.731 --> 01:24:58.332
-[continues indistinctly]
-[engine rumbling]

1581
01:24:58.465 --> 01:25:00.635
[Z]
I used to do meth
in a place like this.

1582
01:25:01.368 --> 01:25:02.502
By the way...

1583
01:25:03.337 --> 01:25:05.607
...you never did tell me
why the no-killing policy.

1584
01:25:06.206 --> 01:25:07.809
Yeah. C. why don't you tell him?

1585
01:25:10.143 --> 01:25:13.113
[woman on advertisement
continues indistinctly]

1586
01:25:15.482 --> 01:25:17.117
[Crilenger]
Used to be agency.

1587
01:25:19.020 --> 01:25:20.287
Last time. our team went to.

1588
01:25:20.788 --> 01:25:23.490
to a village
on a search-and-destroy.

1589
01:25:29.496 --> 01:25:32.600
Killed a lot of kids
and families in the process.

1590
01:25:34.434 --> 01:25:35.870
Territory seized.

1591
01:25:36.838 --> 01:25:39.306
There was a woman...
who survived.

1592
01:25:39.439 --> 01:25:41.676
[somber music]

1593
01:25:46.080 --> 01:25:47.314
We were told...

1594
01:25:48.750 --> 01:25:52.252
...no witnesses.
Our task was to clean...

1595
01:25:53.054 --> 01:25:54.254
...the area.

1596
01:25:57.058 --> 01:25:58.492
I wanted to help her.

1597
01:26:01.129 --> 01:26:04.364
And then. someone from our crew
shot her right there.

1598
01:26:06.433 --> 01:26:07.669
It was Malik.

1599
01:26:08.301 --> 01:26:09.671
Oh. shit.

1600
01:26:11.271 --> 01:26:12.674
I quit after that.

1601
01:26:14.274 --> 01:26:16.209
[inhales deeply]
I made the decision

1602
01:26:16.343 --> 01:26:20.748
never to... kill...
anybody again.

1603
01:26:23.417 --> 01:26:25.520
Most mercs are like Malik.

1604
01:26:26.319 --> 01:26:31.491
I figured.
someone in this business.
so long as it exists...

1605
01:26:33.728 --> 01:26:35.730
...can do it
without all the insanity.

1606
01:26:37.131 --> 01:26:38.231
See?

1607
01:26:40.535 --> 01:26:41.869
That wasn't so hard.

1608
01:26:42.269 --> 01:26:43.403
[sighing] Yeah.

1609
01:26:46.007 --> 01:26:48.810
-[grunts]
-So. how did you two
start working together?

1610
01:26:49.309 --> 01:26:53.748
I was a... grunt
in The Centrals.

1611
01:26:55.983 --> 01:26:57.585
And after discharge...

1612
01:26:59.520 --> 01:27:01.856
...got all fucked up
on drugs and shit.

1613
01:27:02.890 --> 01:27:04.291
Ended up homeless.

1614
01:27:05.358 --> 01:27:06.861
Crilenger helped clean me up.

1615
01:27:07.795 --> 01:27:09.697
Oh. fuck!

1616
01:27:10.131 --> 01:27:11.231
[Crilenger]
What?

1617
01:27:11.364 --> 01:27:12.734
I forgot I have a thing

1618
01:27:12.867 --> 01:27:14.468
I need to go to tomorrow night.

1619
01:27:14.602 --> 01:27:15.870
[exhales] What thing?

1620
01:27:16.003 --> 01:27:18.238
[helicopter blades whirring
in the distance]

1621
01:27:18.371 --> 01:27:19.674
Thing at my boss's house.

1622
01:27:20.407 --> 01:27:22.744
Oh. that's a fucking great idea.

1623
01:27:22.877 --> 01:27:24.812
Oh. yeah. thank you!
That's nice!

1624
01:27:24.946 --> 01:27:27.280
I don't wanna walk into work
on Monday morning

1625
01:27:27.414 --> 01:27:29.150
and have my boss go.
"Hey. Ethan.

1626
01:27:29.282 --> 01:27:30.551
you don't have a job anymore."

1627
01:27:31.351 --> 01:27:33.087
[gunshots on video game]

1628
01:27:33.221 --> 01:27:36.591
["Serenade No. 13 in G Major.
K. 525" by Mozart playing]

1629
01:27:55.076 --> 01:27:57.310
[crickets chirping]

1630
01:27:57.444 --> 01:27:58.546
[Kerry whispers]
What the fuck?

1631
01:27:58.679 --> 01:28:00.915
[footsteps on rooftop]

1632
01:28:02.016 --> 01:28:05.452
-[music increases]
-[gunshots]

1633
01:28:40.021 --> 01:28:40.922
[blade rings]

1634
01:28:58.172 --> 01:29:00.407
[music continues]

1635
01:29:01.209 --> 01:29:02.409
[blade rings]

1636
01:29:05.947 --> 01:29:07.480
[blade rings]

1637
01:29:16.757 --> 01:29:19.060
-[ominous sting]
-[sword ringing echoes]

1638
01:29:19.193 --> 01:29:21.428
[suspenseful music]

1639
01:29:23.331 --> 01:29:25.566
[engine rumbling]

1640
01:29:30.738 --> 01:29:32.874
[indistinct chatter]

1641
01:29:33.007 --> 01:29:35.042
[glasses clinking]

1642
01:29:53.361 --> 01:29:55.630
-Thank you.
-[glass clinks]

1643
01:29:55.763 --> 01:29:57.698
Do you know
where I can find Mr. Wellman?

1644
01:30:03.070 --> 01:30:04.839
That goddamn Collective.

1645
01:30:04.972 --> 01:30:06.741
Uh. C & Earth's in
over their heads.

1646
01:30:06.874 --> 01:30:08.042
Tran and Kerry sent out a team

1647
01:30:08.175 --> 01:30:09.777
to take care of Malik
at Rubicon.

1648
01:30:09.911 --> 01:30:11.846
If you didn't do this
for Peredor.

1649
01:30:11.979 --> 01:30:14.015
this close
to a hostile takeover--

1650
01:30:14.515 --> 01:30:17.251
Pac-Man defense.
Speaking of which.
what happened?

1651
01:30:17.385 --> 01:30:20.655
We're sending every boot we have
to that lab at Aurora.

1652
01:30:20.788 --> 01:30:22.455
We'll recover what was stolen.

1653
01:30:22.823 --> 01:30:24.992
then we're gonna burn it
to the fucking ground.

1654
01:30:25.559 --> 01:30:28.162
Ethan! I'm glad
you could make it.

1655
01:30:28.296 --> 01:30:29.263
Join us!

1656
01:30:29.397 --> 01:30:30.564
Folks. this is Ethan Mason.

1657
01:30:30.698 --> 01:30:32.600
our financial analyst.

1658
01:30:32.733 --> 01:30:35.036
Saving us a whole lot
of trouble.

1659
01:30:35.502 --> 01:30:36.837
I was just doing my job.

1660
01:30:37.605 --> 01:30:39.206
Ethan. Kay Chancellor.

1661
01:30:39.340 --> 01:30:42.043
Chairman of the Board
for Peredor Corporation.

1662
01:30:42.176 --> 01:30:46.180
Hitomi Brazcel.
CEO of Sakura International.

1663
01:30:46.314 --> 01:30:50.051
You've got Senator Brigman.
and Tran. of course.
you already know.

1664
01:30:50.518 --> 01:30:52.853
I hear you're
very talented. Mr. Mason.

1665
01:30:52.987 --> 01:30:55.856
It's definitely a pleasure
to make your acquaintance.

1666
01:30:56.557 --> 01:30:58.059
It's a pleasure
to meet you as well.

1667
01:30:58.659 --> 01:31:00.795
Just like his father. Jack.

1668
01:31:01.494 --> 01:31:02.563
Modest.

1669
01:31:03.230 --> 01:31:04.332
You knew my father?

1670
01:31:04.464 --> 01:31:06.968
Briefly. Y-- you know what?

1671
01:31:07.535 --> 01:31:10.638
I have an incredible
single malt.

1672
01:31:10.771 --> 01:31:13.174
Are you a Scotch man?

1673
01:31:15.977 --> 01:31:17.011
Why not?

1674
01:31:17.144 --> 01:31:18.846
Stellar 50.

1675
01:31:19.780 --> 01:31:20.748
Isn't that expensive?

1676
01:31:20.881 --> 01:31:22.783
-[soft popping]
-Very.

1677
01:31:23.517 --> 01:31:25.786
[soft pouring]

1678
01:31:27.487 --> 01:31:28.589
Thank you.

1679
01:31:29.724 --> 01:31:30.825
What about you?

1680
01:31:32.360 --> 01:31:35.062
I already... got mine.

1681
01:31:37.031 --> 01:31:38.265
To success.

1682
01:31:39.133 --> 01:31:40.034
[clinks]

1683
01:31:41.102 --> 01:31:43.503
[indistinct chatter
in the distance]

1684
01:31:45.439 --> 01:31:47.041
[coughing]

1685
01:31:47.808 --> 01:31:49.110
[chuckles] Good.

1686
01:31:49.243 --> 01:31:50.878
-And strong.
-Mm.

1687
01:31:51.012 --> 01:31:52.747
But it's very smooth. yeah.

1688
01:31:54.015 --> 01:31:55.950
You said that you.
you worked with my father?

1689
01:31:56.584 --> 01:32:00.021
Well. he worked
with an affiliate of ours
many years ago. I...

1690
01:32:00.721 --> 01:32:02.156
...I hope I didn't offend.

1691
01:32:02.289 --> 01:32:03.190
Not at all.

1692
01:32:05.026 --> 01:32:06.227
A tragedy.

1693
01:32:06.894 --> 01:32:10.131
I really don't think
it was his fault.

1694
01:32:13.901 --> 01:32:17.038
-[beeps]
<i>-Welcome back to everyone's</i>
<i>favorite Z dating show.</i>

1695
01:32:17.171 --> 01:32:19.940
<i>Listen. uh. I believe</i>
<i>with your beauty. your talent.</i>

1696
01:32:20.074 --> 01:32:21.909
<i>mixed with my superior genetics.</i>

1697
01:32:22.043 --> 01:32:24.378
<i>we will create</i>
<i>the ultimate apex progeny.</i>

1698
01:32:24.513 --> 01:32:26.414
<i>What would you do if a mage</i>
<i>was attacking her?</i>

1699
01:32:26.547 --> 01:32:28.649
-[beeps]
<i>-Rumor has it</i>
<i>Mutual One made a major play</i>

1700
01:32:28.783 --> 01:32:31.352
<i>and will begin purchasing</i>
<i>majority shares in Peredor.</i>

1701
01:32:31.485 --> 01:32:34.855
<i>Sakura Biotech.</i>
<i>and Tranceworld Media</i>
<i>on Tuesday.</i>

1702
01:32:34.989 --> 01:32:37.526
<i>making their portfolio</i>
<i>the largest in the world.</i>

1703
01:32:37.658 --> 01:32:38.793
<i>-Back to you. Kevin.</i>
-[beeps]

1704
01:32:38.926 --> 01:32:40.027
[ominous music]

1705
01:32:40.161 --> 01:32:41.328
I thought you guys
were trying to--

1706
01:32:41.462 --> 01:32:43.030
Mm. not exactly.

1707
01:32:45.800 --> 01:32:48.202
-You designed it.
-Not me.

1708
01:32:49.136 --> 01:32:51.906
-But that's ill--
-Illegal? I know.

1709
01:32:53.240 --> 01:32:54.175
[softly] I know.

1710
01:32:55.743 --> 01:32:56.777
I don't feel great.

1711
01:32:57.512 --> 01:33:00.648
It's been so long
since I thought about Alan.

1712
01:33:01.082 --> 01:33:03.350
-[glass clatters]
-Boy. was he naive.

1713
01:33:03.484 --> 01:33:06.555
but... highly instrumental.

1714
01:33:06.687 --> 01:33:07.788
What?

1715
01:33:08.355 --> 01:33:09.356
Oh. your dad.

1716
01:33:09.990 --> 01:33:13.961
Amazing how the press bought
that fake suicide of his.

1717
01:33:14.862 --> 01:33:18.165
Man. we made a lot
of money off that one.

1718
01:33:18.866 --> 01:33:20.334
[clattering and thudding]

1719
01:33:20.468 --> 01:33:22.703
[waves crashing]

1720
01:33:27.374 --> 01:33:29.610
[engine rumbling]

1721
01:33:30.377 --> 01:33:32.379
[grunting]

1722
01:33:36.784 --> 01:33:39.353
-[beeping]
-[softly] Get him.

1723
01:33:40.855 --> 01:33:41.655
[woman sighs]

1724
01:33:41.789 --> 01:33:43.257
[engine starts]

1725
01:33:43.390 --> 01:33:45.626
[music continues]

1726
01:33:47.562 --> 01:33:50.131
[both panting]

1727
01:33:53.568 --> 01:33:54.802
[gun cocks]

1728
01:33:58.540 --> 01:34:00.207
-[gunshots]
-[both groan]

1729
01:34:00.341 --> 01:34:01.342
[thudding]

1730
01:34:15.856 --> 01:34:19.260
-[beeping]
-[Z grunts. softly] Hey.

1731
01:34:19.960 --> 01:34:21.962
He's ten sheets
to a fucking hurricane.

1732
01:34:22.897 --> 01:34:24.965
[Crilenger]
Hurry. we have
to get him back in the car.

1733
01:34:27.067 --> 01:34:29.303
-[ominous music]
-[snorting]

